  "body": "/kind bug\r\n\r\n**What happened**:\r\nAfter a cluster is created using kube-up.sh, it is configured using `--bootstrap-kubeconfig`, so it uses the initial certificates referenced in `/var/lib/kubelet/bootstrap-kubeconfig`, which are `/etc/srv/kubernetes/pki/kubelet.crt` and `/etc/srv/kubernetes/pki/kubelet.key`. These files containing the certificate and key are installed world readable on the node:\r\n\r\n```sh\r\n$ ls -l /etc/srv/kubernetes/pki\r\ntotal 12\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1229 Sep  8 00:33 ca-certificates.crt\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1229 Sep  8 00:33 kubelet.crt\r\n-rw-r--r-- 1 root root 1675 Sep  8 00:33 kubelet.key\r\n```\r\n\r\n**What you expected to happen**:\r\nThe key especially, should be installed with more restricted permissions, possibly even deleted after the initial bootstrap use.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (as minimally and precisely as possible)**:\r\n```sh\r\ncluster/kube-up.sh\r\n```\r\n\r\n**Anything else we need to know?**:\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n- Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n```sh\r\n$ kubectl version\r\nClient Version: version.Info{Major:\"1\", Minor:\"9+\", GitVersion:\"v1.9.0-alpha.0.425+7e5d2df2995ef4-dirty\", GitCommit:\"7e5d2df2995ef402a2e4ee39524c761904bf7689\", GitTreeState:\"dirty\", BuildDate:\"2017-09-08T00:24:44Z\", GoVersion:\"go1.8.3\", Compiler:\"gc\", Platform:\"linux/amd64\"}\r\n```\r\n\r\n- Cloud provider or hardware configuration**:\r\n- OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n- Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n- Install tools:\r\n- Others:\r\n",
